Happy 5th birthday to the  girl who made me a mama oh my bad.. it's not mama it's Mimi 🙂

 from the day you were born, you’ve been teaching me how to love harder, laugh louder, and slow down when it matters. I thought I’d be showing you the way, but turns out you’ve been leading me all along.

You somehow always know when someone needs a hug or a little check-in… You’ve got this quiet, grown-up kindness that blows me away.

You’re silly, sweet, full of sparkle and the best sister Aani could ask for. Even when she steals your things, you just smile and let her. You make it look easy.

I love how you walk into a room and bring joy just by being you. You’re magic, my baby. And watching you grow is the greatest gift of my life.
Every day with you feels like a page from a fairy tale.

We love you so much, birthday girl. Forever our light, forever our Princess Kiana. 👑💕
